==Hindi==
===Etymology===
Sanskrit <!-- both McGregor and Platts say it is from Sankrit with no more detail which I presume means it is from अकाल, but neither Cappellers or Monier Williams Sanskrit dictionaries have that as a Sanskrit word.-->

===Adjective===
'''अकाल''' akāl {{m}}
# untimely, unseasonable, inopportune, premature

===Noun ===
'''अकाल''' akāl {{m}}
# an inopportune or unseasonable time
# untimeliness, unseasonableness; 
# a bad season, a season of scarcity
# drought, scarcity, dearth, famine
# extremity, pinch

